jobDescription:
Datalogic is currently hiring Automation Testing Engineers across Junior, Middle, Senior, and Lead levels to support the development of our products.Role Main activities

- Draw sketches of product ideas and design mockups of proposed products;
- Contribute to define detailed project requirements and specifications;
- Define the action plan within the product development in terms of the needed time/resources;
- Develop the assigned parts of the project, paying attention to the guidelines provided by the team leaders
- Contribute to the validation-test plans, perform measurements and functional tests on prototypes, assuring full coverage of all requirements;
- Ensure design files and technical documentation are kept up to date and stored in accordance with departmental procedures;
- Embrace innovation culture of our Company, contributing to generate invention disclosures and to scout/evaluate novel and differentiating technologies;
- Participate in the maintenance of existing products, with the aim also to solve problems arisen from field or production.

Job Details & Specifications

- Collaborate to the test activities with planning, progress tracking, and test coverage analysis.
- Monitors project status, test coverage, and test case/defect quality. Analyzes project cost, efficiency, and risks.
- Collaborates with development team to define test requirements, cases, and timelines.
- Collaborate with development teams to understand requirements and resolve testing issues.
- Conducts and oversees various testing types (functional, regression, performance).
- Analyzes test results and drives continuous improvement of testing processes.
- Provides weekly project updates and reports, including achievements, issues, and risks

